{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And it came to pass, as he went into the house of one of the chief Pharisees to eat bread on the sabbath day, that they watched him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And, behold, there was a certain man before him which had the dropsy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus answering spake unto the lawyers and Pharisees,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "saying",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they held their peace. And he took him, and healed him, and let him go;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "saying",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they could not answer him again to these things."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he put forth a parable to those which were bidden, when he marked how they chose out the chief rooms;"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "saying unto them",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Parable of Humility"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Then said he also to him that bade him",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Teaching on Hospitality"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when one of them that sat at meat with him heard these things,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "he said unto him, Blessed is he that shall eat bread in the kingdom of God.",
          "speaker": "Unknown Guest"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Then said he unto him",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And there went great multitudes with him: and he turned,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "and said unto them",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Cost of Discipleship"
      ]
    }
  ]
}